This paper discusses the incorporation of consciousness into AI systems, which is a topic that falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the functional role of consciousness in learning and behavioral control, which relates to the sub-categories of robotics (cs.RO) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions reinforcement learning, which is a sub-field of machine learning and falls under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the ethical implications of creating conscious AI systems, which relates to the sub-category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
